  %body
    %h1 Simple Grapher
    #chart
    #description
      %h2 About the Graph
      %ul
        %li Drag on the canvas to translate/pan the graph.
        %li double-click on the canvas to zoom in
        %li shift-double-click on the canvas to zoom out
        %li Drag on one of the X or Y axis numeric labels to re-scale that axis
        %li click on a data point to select it
        %li drag a selected data point to change it's value
        %li enter the delete or backspace key to delete a selected data point
        %li drag a selected data point to change it's value
        %li hold the ALT/Option key down and click an empty area of the graph to add a data point
      %p
        %em
          source:
          %a{:href => "https://gist.github.com/1182434"} gist.github.com/1182434
      %p
        There's still a bug where if you scale an axis once, you
        can then translate/pan around but if you scale the same axis
        a second time when you next try and translate/pan the result
        of the first axis re-scale will re-appear. This bug also
        appears if you re-scale the axes and then add a new data
        point.
